- VSCode Version: Version 1.11.0-insider (1.11.0-insider) 05f19eec2042555ca04e5f014befa95248a65fe9
- OS Version: all

We are using the `vscode.languages.registerDocumentLinkProvider` like this:

``` javascript
vscode.languages.registerDocumentLinkProvider({language: 'wallaby-output'}, {
        provideDocumentLinks: doc => {
          ...
        }
});
```

where the `wallaby-output` is our output channel language name with `"text/x-code-output"` `mimetype`:

```
"contributes": {
    ...
    "languages": [
      {
        "id": "wallaby-output",
        "mimetypes": [
          "text/x-code-output"
        ]
      }
    ],
    ...
  },
```

In v1.10.2, the `provideDocumentLinks` is invoked as expected and we are able to add links in our output channel:
<img width="498" alt="screen shot 2017-03-20 at 3 30 50 pm" src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/979966/24089437/64e41d6c-0d82-11e7-8843-8bf865acd52c.png">

In the insiders build Version 1.11.0-insider 05f19eec2042555ca04e5f014befa95248a65fe9, the `provideDocumentLinks` is not invoked anymore, so output channel can not provide links anymore:
![screen shot 2017-03-20 at 3 31 23 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/979966/24089473/ce0f37fe-0d82-11e7-9770-923137bb28ec.png)

- VSCode Version: 1.10.2
- OS Version: Windows 10 Home 64bit 

Steps to Reproduce:

1. Create new file with extension .cpp (example.cpp)
2. Past code into document and save. 

```
void bar()
{
    int foo = 0;
    if (foo)
    {
        foo = 1;
    }
}
```

3. [alt]+[shift]+F to "format document" 

Expected the output to stay the same. Got the following output 

```
void bar()
{
    int foo = 0;
    if (foo)
    {
    foo = 1;
    }
}
```
